  <header class="step-hero ">
    <div class="container-page step-hero__inner">
      <nav class="step-breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> <span>/</span> <a href="/the-8-steps/">The 8 Steps</a> <span>/</span> <span>Smart Stewards</span></nav>
      <span class="step-num" style="color:var(--color-blue)">01</span>
      <span class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--color-blue)">Phase 1 · Live in it · College Planning</span>
      <h1 class="display-xl step-hero__title">Smart Stewards</h1>
      <p class="lede step-hero__lede">The Stairway begins before you ever own a home. Smart Stewards is about teaching the next generation — and yourself — to treat money as something to steward wisely, not just spend. For families, it starts with college planning: funding education without derailing the wealth you're building.</p>
      <div class="step-progress mono">Step 01 of 08 · The Student</div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <article class="container-prose prose-editorial step-body" set:html={`<h2><b>What the Smart Stewards step means</b></h2><p>This first rung is about foundations. It's where families plan for college costs, teach financial literacy, and make early decisions that compound for decades. Stewardship means handling what you have with wisdom and intention — the mindset that carries through all eight steps.</p><h2><b>Who this step is for</b></h2><ul><li>Parents planning for a child's education</li><li>Young adults learning to handle money with intention</li><li>Families who want to fund college without sacrificing long-term wealth</li><li>Anyone laying the financial foundation before homeownership</li></ul><h2><b>The shift</b></h2><p>The shift here is from spending to stewarding — from reacting to money to directing it with purpose.</p><h2><b>How Stairway helps</b></h2><p>We help families think through college funding in the context of their whole financial picture — so paying for education doesn't come at the cost of the home and wealth steps ahead. It starts with a conversation about your goals, not a product.</p><h2><b>Frequently Asked Questions</b></h2><h3><b>What does the Smart Stewards step mean?</b></h3><p>This first rung is about foundations. It's where families plan for college costs, teach financial literacy, and make early decisions that compound for decades. Stewardship means handling what you have with wisdom and intention — the mindset that carries through all eight steps.</p><h3><b>Who is the Smart Stewards step for?</b></h3><p>It's for parents planning for a child's education, and others making this transition. The shift here is from spending to stewarding — from reacting to money to directing it with purpose.</p><h3><b>How do I move to the next step?</b></h3><p>The next rung is First-Time Home Buyer — The First Door. We can help you take the next step when you're ready.</p>`} />

